commitResults.messageTitle: Set member availability command: Improve parsing and ease of use
commitResults.messageBody:
Currently, availability values are implemented as a string.
This brings several problems. The string is hard to sort, hard to
parse and verify validity. Having to type in the names of days is
also tedious when the user could just type "d/1 2 3" instead to
represent the days. Using numbers which can be converted to
DayOfWeek makes it easier to parse and validate.

Let's use java.time.DayOfWeek and change the data type of
availability values from String to List<DayOfWeek> as well as change
the command format to improve ease of use and validation.

Add command to allocate member to a facility on a given day.
Checks for valid member and facility indices given, whether
the member is available on that day, whether the facility
is at max capacity and whether the person is already allocated to
the facility. However, does not check whether member is
assigned to different facilities on the same day and each member
can only be allocated to a facility once regardless of day.

Checks whether a member has been allocated to a facility before
deallocating the member.

commitResults.messageTitle: Facility Class: Add logical constraints to fields
commitResults.messageBody:
Adding more constraints to the fields of Facility class would make
it more realistic and less prone to errors. Changing the time to
display am/pm instead of 24h makes it more user-friendly. Displaying
the current capacity/max capacity is more useful.

Let's,
* update VALIDATION_REGEX to limit FacilityName and Location to
  50 alphanumeric characters
* update VALIDATION_REGEX to limite Time to valid 24h format HHmm
* change FacilityListCard to display current capacity
* update VALIDATION_REGEX to limit Capacity to be a positive integer
  up to 50

Update tests to conform with new constraints and field formats
and improve coverage.
